":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   James   and   Jacob .  In French there is no distinction between a form corresponding to <i>Jacob</i> and a form corresponding to <i>James</i>. This is a perennially popular French given name, and <i>Jacques</i> or <i>Jacques Bonhomme</i> has been used (like <i>John Bull</i> in English) as a typification of the ordinary citizen. In  Shakespeare's  time it was also used as an English name, pronounced ‘<b>jay</b>-kwez’, as in the case of the melancholy character Jacques in As You Like It. Though rarely, if ever, now used in Britain it is found in the United States."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Jacques de Lambinus was born about 1066, in Scotland, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1066–":"umbes 1066–Surnud","1086–Male":"1086–Surnud","1066–Male":"1066–Surnud","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","about 1066":"umbes 1066","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1066–":"noin 1066–Kuollut","1086–Male":"1086–Kuollut","1066–Male":"1066–Kuollut","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","about 1066":"noin 1066","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1066–":"environ 1066–Décédé","1086–Male":"1086–Décédé","1066–Male":"1066–Décédé","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","about 1066":"environ 1066","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Jacques de Lambinus est né environ 1066, à Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1066–":"um 1066–Verstorben","1086–Male":"1086–Verstorben","1066–Male":"1066–Verstorben","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","about 1066":"um 1066","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Schottland, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Jacques de Lambinus wurde um 1066 in Schottland, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindeste